"Strike" here means to strikeout a vote (slash it) so as to mark is as not being counted. E.g. a user voted a second time; a user was not eligible for voting because of an insufficient edit count; a known sockpuppet was used, and the puppetmaster also voted; a bot user vote, etc.

securepoll-urandom-not-supported:
As to the meaning of ''cryptographic random number'', see [[:wikipedia:Cryptographically secure pseudorandom number generator]] for reference.

The /dev/urandom cryptographic random number generation device is not supported on servers running Microsoft Windows. On other platforms the [[MediaWiki:Securepoll-dump-no-urandom/en|Securepoll-dump-no-urandom]] message is generated if opening of the /dev/urandom device fails.
